Third-party components
----------------------

The `cpp/ddl/` directory contains C++ headers copied (snapshot date 2026-02-12)
from the Daedalus project by Galois, Inc.:

    https://github.com/GaloisInc/daedalus  (rts-c/ddl/)

    - boxed.h    (verbatim)
    - debug.h    (verbatim)
    - maybe.h    (verbatim)
    - size.h     (verbatim)
    - map.h      (one verification-local modification, see below)

Daedalus is distributed under the BSD 3-Clause License. Each header retains
a comment identifying its upstream source.

`cpp/ddl/map.h` carries a single, clearly-marked, behaviour-preserving change
for verification: the 12 *uses* of the `Node::black`/`Node::red` colour
constants are replaced by the literals `false`/`true` (each marked with a
`/*black*/` or `/*red*/` comment; the constant definitions are unchanged). This
folds the constants to literals in the cpp2v-generated AST, avoiding a
static-initialization modelling gap in BRiCk, with no change in behaviour
(`Color` is `bool` and the constants ARE `false`/`true`). See the NOTE at the
top of `Node` in `map.h` for how to revert to verbatim upstream.

The Coq/Rocq proofs depend on BRiCk, the open-source C++ separation-logic
framework:

    https://github.com/bedrocksystems/BRiCk

BRiCk is not vendored in this repository; it is built separately (see README).
Only the publicly-available components of BRiCk are used; no proprietary
packages (e.g. `skylabs.auto`) are required.
